Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaeanorendarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/picon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/30/01 3:25:34 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root Nuking Soloing</span><hr size=1> Bah - I root/nuked all the way to 45. I liked to play busy areas where it was all too easy to pick up adds kiting, so I would just pull them somewhere reasonably safe, root, and start blasting. When it broke (and when you use it a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> lot</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> you realize it's nothing like as horrible as people make it out to be. Many fights it would never break at all), it the critter was stunnable, I'd stun, step back, and re-root; if not, stand there bravely and re-root in-between whackings. I used up a lot of Jasper and bandages, but I did this for a long time. There is an art to learning what mobs to avoid, and which ones are beatable but not worth the effort, but that comes with some trial and error. I did, however, like to stay within running distance of a zone line for those times things went really badly. <p><table><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#cc0000 strength=1)><font size=2 color=#ffff00 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uadoryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adoryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/30/01 11:36:52 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://adoryn.com/junk/icon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root Nuking Soloing</span><hr size=1> It's a lot easier to solo with a snare and with sow, but they aren't necessary. You just need to be more observant and careful without them.<br>
<br>
- Always use a damage absorber (shieldskin, steelskin, whatever)<br>
- Pick a good location where you're not as likely to get adds (and once you start fighting, make good use of that view key to make sure no adds are heading your way while fighting)<br>
- Start with root and be ready to re-cast it if it breaks (which it probably will)<br>
- Keep stacks of bandages around for close calls (especially if you're dotted)<br>
<br>
A lot of my wizard friends thought I was crazy to not bother buying sow potions, because that's the only way they'd solo, but I rarely ran into situations where it would have been worth the cost. Maybe I've just had a lot of practice, but it's rather uncommon for me to die while soloing. <p><center><table border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center>
